<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-451-964  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 451 964.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Communications  June 1989 v12 n3 p158(9).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Design and performance evaluation of an optical fibre LAN withdouble token rings. (local area network) (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Casale, Salvatore; Catania, Vincenzo; Faro, Alberto; Parchenkov,Nikolai; Vita, Lorenzo.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Deterministic Access Fibre Network, an optical fibre localarea network which aims to offer a set of services including datatransmission, sound and images, is presented.andP;  The topology is ofthe ring type, on which there are active nodes based on theInternational Organization for Standardization Open systemsInterconnection architecture, with access complying with the IEEE802.5 token-ring standard.andP;  To increase throughput, and to makethe network highly reliable, a two-fibre cable forming twocounter-rotating rings is installed.andP;  First, the hardware andsoftware architecture adopted for a typical DAFNE node isdiscussed, then a methodology to aid the designer in choosing theoptimal LAN configuration according to the user's needs by ahighly interactive and automated environment is outlined.andO;Finally, analytical and simulation approaches are shown forperformance evaluation of the Medium Access Control layer.andO;(Reprinted by permission of the publisher.)andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Local Area NetworksFiber OpticsToken Ring NetworksCatania, Universita diDesign.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Hardware structure of generic station i. (chart)Connection-oriented channels. (chart)Station software architecture. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>